# Mac Control Plane (mandatory)

Read `~/Desktop/MacLaw/MAC_CONTROL_PLANE_LOCKED.md` when Mac, SourceA, factory, hub, or cloud is in scope.

## Law

- **Mac** = control panel only (Hub :13020, Routing :8780, Mac Law :8781, Cursor steering)
- **Cloud + APIs** = all factory compute (FBE Railway, Supabase, loop specialist, OpenRouter on cloud)

## Agents MUST

1. Keep `~/.sina/mac-control-plane-v1.flag` present during founder sessions
2. Keep `~/.sina/cli-disabled-v1.flag` — no local CLI drain on Mac body
3. Keep `~/.sina/api-disabled-v1.flag` **absent** — Mac may call cloud APIs
4. Keep factory mode **FREEZE** — never bootstrap `com.sourcea.autorun-worker` without ASF
5. Route ACT/implement/build work to cloud workers — not `fbe_motor_delegate_v1` on Mac
6. **Founder session: NO heavy validators/E2E** — no `validate-all-e2e`, no surfaces E2E, no recipe `--build`, no Playwright/Chrome debug stacks while founder works in Cursor
7. **INCIDENT-039 RED FLAG:** NEVER stuck in validators on Mac — reply <30s · one light check ≤90s · proof=receipts · 11+ min = P0 harm

## Boot

```bash
bash ~/Desktop/SourceA/scripts/enter-mac-control-plane-v1.sh
bash ~/Desktop/SourceA/scripts/validate-mac-control-plane-v1.sh
```

